Peru Stocks: Casa Grande, La Pampilla, Maple, Minsur Decline

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-08-10T21:10:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/peru-stocks-casa-grande-la-pampilla-maple-minsur-decline.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:55 p.m. New York time.  The Lima General Index fell 1.3 percent to 18,969.23. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index fell 1.7 percent to 2,410.97.  Mining and energy companies declined amid concern a
worsening sovereign debt crisis in  Europe  and slower than
expected U.S. growth will curtail demand for commodities.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1)  (MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin
producer, fell for the seventh time in eight sessions, shedding
5.6 percent to 3.02 soles.  Maple Energy Plc. (MPLE)  , the oil
and natural gas producer with operations in Peru, fell 3.9
percent to $1, a one-month low. Refineria la Pampilla SA
(RELAPAC1 PE), Peru’s largest petroleum refinery, declined 2.5
percent to 78 centimos. Corp. Aceros Arequipa SA (CORAREI1 PE),
the Lima-based steelmaker, fell 2.6 percent to 2.24 soles.  Sugar producers weakened as prices for the sweetener fell
as much as 4 percent.  Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest sugar producer,
fell 1.8 percent to 14 soles, a five-week low. Empresa
Agroindustrial Pomalca SA (POMALCC1 PE) slid 2.2 percent to 45
centimos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
